Ad Text:
Company description:



Deloitte Services Pty Ltd



Job description:




ITS EDW Data Engineer | Data & Analytics | Sydney, AUS

Work on cutting-edge enterprise data solutions using Databricks, Azure Data Factory, DBT, and Python.

Collaborate with a high-performing, agile team to deliver impactful insights across Deloitte.

Continuous professional growth through mentoring, training, and exposure to emerging data engineering technologies.

Deloitte Technology is seeking a skilled Data Engineer to join our Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) team in Sydney. This is a permanent role where you'll play a key part in designing, implementing, and optimising scalable data pipelines and workflows that power Deloitte's data-driven initiatives. You'll have the opportunity to work closely with EDW pod leads and the Senior Data Engineering Manager, contributing to high-impact projects across the business.

What will your typical day look like?

Day to day you will:

Develop and maintain scalable data pipelines using Databricks and Azure Data Factory.

Transform raw data into actionable insights using Data Build Tools (DBT) and Python.

Build and maintain data integrations across systems using APIs.

Monitor and optimise workflows for performance and cost-efficiency.

Lead project delivery pods, mentor junior team members, and conduct code reviews.

Collaborate with data modelers, analysts, DBAs, DevOps, and infrastructure teams to deliver high-quality solutions.

Document processes, workflows, and system architecture to maintain clarity and knowledge sharing.

About the team

Deloitte Technology's EDW team powers enterprise-wide data initiatives, enabling business users to make informed, data-driven decisions. You'll join a collaborative and high-performing team working in an agile environment, tackling complex data challenges and continuously improving the EDW platform.

Enough about us, let's talk about you

You may have all or some of the following skills / experiences:

5+ years of experience in data engineering, with expertise in Databricks, SQL, Python, Azure Data Factory, and DBT.

Experience designing, building, and optimising data pipelines and workflows.

Hands-on experience with API-based data integrations and version control systems (Azure DevOps, GitHub).

Strong understanding of data architecture patterns and cloud data storage solutions.

Excellent problem-solving skills, attention to detail, and adaptability.

Collaborative mindset with strong communication and stakeholder management skills.

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field. Advanced degrees or relevant certifications in Azure or Databricks are a plus.

Desirable: Knowledge of Azure Fabric and emerging data engineering technologies.

Why Deloitte?

At Deloitte, we focus our energy on interesting and impactful work. We're always learning, innovating, and setting the standard; making a positive difference to our clients and society. We put coaching at the heart of what we do, helping our people grow their careers in any direction - up, into new areas, or across the globe.

We embrace diversity, equity, and inclusion. We have a diverse collection of people from different backgrounds, experiences, abilities, and thinking styles. What binds us together is a shared commitment to value everyone's perspective and cultivate inclusion, making our work environment a space where everyone belongs.

We support flexibility and choice. We encourage you to find the right balance between connecting in person with your clients and teams and meeting your own personal needs.

We help you live and work well. To support your personal and professional life, we offer a range of perks and benefits, including retail discounts, wellbeing leave, paid volunteering days, twelve flexible working options, market-leading parental leave, and a return-to-work support package.

Next Steps

Sound like the sort of role for you? Apply now, we'd love to hear from you!

Job Title: AI Solutions Engineer (Microsoft Copilot & Power Platform)
Ad Text:
We're looking for an AI Solutions Engineer to join a growing Business Applications team within a Microsoft-first environment.

This role is all about applied AI. You'll be designing and deploying AI solutions into the business using Microsoft Copilot Studio, Azure services and the Power Platform. These are real solutions in production, not experimentation or custom model research.

If you're currently working with Copilot, building agents, understanding how AI solutions are designed and governed, and want to be closer to the business impact of what you build, this role will suit you.

What you'll be doing
Designing and delivering AI solutions using Microsoft Copilot Studio
Working closely with Senior AI Engineers and architects on solution design
Overseeing architecture and design where delivery partners build the solution
Ensuring governance, standards and scalability across AI and Power Platform solutions
Collaborating with business stakeholders to understand problems and translate them into technical solutions
Supporting and evolving the existing Power Platform environment without being a support or ticket-based role
Working alongside data and architecture teams on AI solution integration


What we're looking for
Hands-on experience with Microsoft Copilot Studio
Strong Power Platform foundations
Experience using Azure services with a solid understanding of backend architecture
Ability to explain how AI agents are designed, built and governed
Comfortable discussing architecture, tech stack and solution design
Background as a developer, or someone who has transitioned from development into Power Platform or consulting
Strong communication skills and confidence working with business stakeholders



This is a hybrid role, with 2-3 days per wek on-site in Surry Hills.

Unfortunately, we cannot offer sponsorship for this role.

About Powerhouse

Powerhouse Museum is located at the intersection of arts, design, science, and technology and plays a critical role in engaging communities with contemporary ideas and issues. It is the custodian of more than half a million objects of national and international significance and is considered one of the finest and most diverse collections in Australia. We are undertaking a landmark $1.3 billion infrastructure renewal program, led by the creation of Powerhouse Parramatta; expanded research and public facilities at Powerhouse Castle Hill; the heritage revitalisation of the iconic Powerhouse Ultimo; and the ongoing operation of Sydney Observatory.

About the role

The Integration Engineer is responsible for designing, developing, and supporting secure, reliable and scalable integrations across the museum’s enterprise technology landscape. The role focuses on API development, middleware services, event-based integration and data exchange patterns to enable seamless interoperability between platforms including DAMS, CMS, CRM, ERP, DataHub and digital experience systems. The role ensures that integration solutions align with enterprise architecture, security standards, and operational requirements, enabling efficient data and digital asset flows across the organisation.

Macquarie University, Wallumattagal Campus, North Ryde | Hybrid Ways of Working

Macquarie University is seeking an innovative and forward-thinking Full Stack Developer to step into a newly created role dedicated to building and scaling our AI enablement capability.

About the role

As a Full Stack Developer, you will be responsible to develop, test, deploy and maintain Generative AI enabled solutions, ensuring alignment with strategic goals and to ensure services perform to stakeholder expectations of reliability, resilience and efficiency. In addition to the development, you will provide technical support and advice to users with Generative AI enabled solutions.

You will be part of a newly created AI Enablement team within IT and will play a crucial role in integrating AI solutions across various faculties and departments, driving forward the University's strategic objectives. The team will develop, implement and support AI initiatives and projects across the University, encouraging innovation and enhancing academic and operational excellence through the application of artificial intelligence technologies.

Reporting to the Manager, AI Enablement, you will:

Co-ordinate and execute the design, development, implementation, operation and user training for Generative AI solutions across all domains of the organisation

Develop Proof of Concept Gen-AI solutions in Azure or AWS

Set up, run and monitor automated test plans and scenarios and report test results to internal stakeholders

Deploy approved solutions in production environment

Review and maintain solution performance dashboards. Iterate solution design based on metrics and user feedback

Develop and maintain solution templates for future scaling

Generate a consistent and intuitive User Interface to ensure a uniform User experience across the university

Create & maintain comprehensive documentation for AI models, APIs, and deployment processes

Engage with vendors and technology groups to stay abreast of the technology learning curve

Comply with relevant EEO and WHS regulations. Implement data privacy and security measures in compliance with university policies and regulations

Perform any other duties as required and appropriate for this classification

About You

You are a skilled Full Stack Developer with a strong background in developing, testing, deploying, and maintaining AI-enabled solutions.

Your strong foundation in software development methodologies, version control, and best practices, coupled with your knowledge of regulatory requirements and ethical considerations in AI, such as GDPR, CCPA, and HIPAA, makes you a technical expert in the field.

You are committed to ongoing professional development and have demonstrated experience working in higher education institutions. Your collaborative approach and problem-solving skills enable you to effectively engage with stakeholders, support project implementation, and drive innovation across the university.

Bachelor's degree in a related discipline or equivalent knowledge, skills and minimum 5 year experience with a demonstrated commitment to ongoing professional development.

Proficiency in programming languages, including Python, JavaScript, and familiarity with R where applicable.

Experience with Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques and libraries for text generation, understanding, and manipulation.

Proficiency in cloud platforms, particularly AWS and Azure.

Experience deploying AI solutions via APIs and integrating cloud-based AI services from multiple vendors.

Strong understanding of CI/CD pipelines, version control (Git), and DevOps workflows.

Experience with containerization and orchestration (Docker, Kubernetes) for deploying scalable AI solutions in Azure and AWS.

Experience developing intuitive front-end interfaces using modern frontend frameworks (e.g. React).

Experience in incident response, resolution, and post-incident analysis of major incidents by applying best practices, including model versioning, monitoring, and lifecycle management.

Desirable:

Relevant Microsoft certifications.

Familiarity with frameworks for LLM development, such as LangChain, LlamaIndex, or similar AI orchestration tools.

Demonstrated knowledge of Prompt engineering for programming.

How to Apply

To be considered, please apply online with your CV and a cover letter outlining how your experience aligns with the selection criteria (above).

We Are Seeking

A proactive Data & Analytics Engineer to join our lean data team. In this mid-level role, you’ll maintain and enhance reporting in SQL and PowerBI, implement end-to-end ETL pipelines in Microsoft Fabric, and  consult stakeholders to shape and deliver requirements, project plans, and data extracts. Ideal candidates have solid data engineering experience and strong data-analysis skills and are eager to tackle everything from database management to developing a customer data model.




Role Overview
As a Data & Analytics Engineer in IT, you’ll partner with the Data Lead, Senior Data Engineer and Data Analyst to deliver actionable insights, streamline processes, and uphold data quality across NobleOak’s analytics platform. You will have the following key responsibilities:

Reporting & Analytics
Develop, maintain and optimise SQL stored procedures and views, Power BI reports, SSRS, and paginated Fabric reports.
Gather business requirements and translate them into new or enhanced SQL stored procedures, views and tables.
Provide ad‑hoc data quickly and accurately to business units such as Marketing, Sales, Client Services, Finance, Risk & Compliance, and Actuarial.
Database Management
Maintain Microsoft SQL Server and Microsoft Fabric Data Warehouses.
Maintain data ingestion SSIS packages for on-premises‑premises SQL Server.
Assist the Senior Data Engineer in maintaining and enhancing our metadata driven‑driven ETL framework and pipelines in Microsoft Fabric.
Translate business requirements into logical, relational data models, aligning database structures with reporting and analytics needs.
Stakeholder Management & Project Planning
Learn key source systems, their relationships, and the value of their data for different stakeholders.
Help stakeholders understand and refine their requirements into actionable work for the data team.
Champion Agile methodology, including sprint planning through Epics, User Stories, and Tasks.
Collaborate with the Senior Data Engineer to produce technical documentation that bridges high‑level stakeholder requirements with actionable technical designs.
Data Governance & Documentation
Maintain the technical solution used to measure data quality across critical data elements.
Produce and maintain clear documentation for pipelines, procedures and models.
Team Support, Development & Mentorship
Learn from and support the Senior Data Engineer in the areas of data architecture, security configuration, and data modelling.
Apply AI productively and safely at work.
Mentor data analysts on tools, processes, and development standards.
Share team responsibilities such as reviewing work, hosting huddles, and creating tickets.



Desired Skills & Experience

3 – 5 years SQL experience, in particular translating complex logic into stored procedures.
Good understanding of ETL design patterns and Microsoft Fabric or Azure Data Factory.
Proven experience building and optimising Power BI reports and semantic models.
Experience maintaining SQL Server and cloud databases (SSIS, ADF pipelines).
Experience with Microsoft Fabric/Databricks, Data Governance, and Azure DevOps CI/CD.
Experience with Python and object orientated programming.
Strong communication skills for liaising with technical and non-technical stakeholders.

Qualifications

Bachelor’s or master’s degree in Computer Science, Data Science, IT or related field.
2–5 years in data engineering or analytics roles, preferably within financial services or technology.
Demonstrated ability to work in a fast-paced, collaborative environment with a “can-do” attitude.
Bonus: Relevant certifications (Fabric Data Analytics Engineer Associate, Fabric Data Engineer Associate, etc).

Overview

Azure Resource Graph’s (ARG part of ARM(Azure Resouure Manager)/Azure Control plane) mission is to reliably organize the planet-scale cloud inventory and making it accessible to every Azure customer through scalable, and performant tools.

ARG is the Inventory of cloud resources, dependencies, services, apps & Azure metadata and is a core service enabling almost all Azure experiences and workloads that are running on top of Azure. Azure Portal, Azure Market Place, Search, Catalog at-scale experiences scenarios for every single Azure customer are powered by ARG. It provides a single pane of glass to query cloud resources via a set of flexible standards with rich scalable, efficient constructs. These standards and toolsets are used by large customers and first party teams alike. ARG’s vision is to enable any customer (large to small) to organize, govern, secure, manage and explore their environments at-scale. Anything we design, develop, or deliver aligns with this vision. As of today, we return close to 6.5+ billion cloud resources per day through these standards to our customers and independent software vendors. This position is one of the core engineering functions and sits right in the center of the platform enabling various other connected engineering functions.

As a Software Engineer II - Azure Resource Graph, you will design, develop, and maintain high-quality, scalable code across the stack while owning features end-to-end—from design and implementation to testing and safe rollout using feature flags. You’ll create clarity around your feature’s goals and technical approach, driving innovation and scalability in execution. In addition, you’ll identify and automate repetitive tasks using AI and scripting tools to boost team productivity and engineering velocity.

Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.

Responsibilities

Works with appropriate stakeholders to determine user requirements for a set of features.

Contributes to the identification of dependencies, and the development of design documents for a product area with little oversight.

Creates and implements code for a product, service, or feature, reusing code as applicable.

Contributes to efforts to break down larger work items into smaller work items and provides estimation.

Acts as a Designated Responsible Individual (DRI) working on-call to monitor system/product feature/service for degradation, downtime, or interruptions and gains approval to restore system/product/service for simple problems.

Remains current in skills by investing time and effort into staying abreast of current developments that will improve the availability, reliability, efficiency, observability, and performance of products while also driving consistency in monitoring and operations at scale. 

Qualifications

Required Qualifications:

Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, or related technical discipline with proven experience coding in languages including, but not limited to, C, C++, C#, Java, JavaScript, or Python

OR equivalent experience.

Other Requirements:

Ability to meet Microsoft, customer and/or government security screening requirements are required for this role. These requirements include, but are not limited to the following specialized security screenings: 

Microsoft Cloud Background Check: This position will be required to pass the Microsoft Cloud Background Check upon hire/transfer and every two years thereafter.

Preferred Qualifications:

Master's Degree in Computer Science or related technical field with proven experience coding in languages including, but not limited to, C, C++, C#, Java, JavaScript, or Python

OR Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science or related technical field AND 2+ years technical engineering experience with coding in languages including, but not limited to, C, C++, C#, Java, JavaScript, or Python

OR equivalent experience.

2+ years:

of Platform Engineering Skills in the area of Distributed Systems and Large-scale Storage Systems Interactions,

AND deep hands-on working knowledge of building a true cloud-scale services,

AND operational experience in running your service in one of the large-scale clouds like Azure or other cloud provider.

1+ year(s) of experience:

in driving designs along with execution and accountability to deliver,

AND in applying AI/ML techniques to large-scale telemetry or resource data,

AND integrating LLM (large language model)-based solutions (e.g., Azure OpenAI, LangChain) into cloud products to improve user experience and operational efficiency.

Understanding of prompt engineering, embedding generation, and vector-based search (e.g., using Azure AI Search or equivalent) to enable intelligent querying.

Senior AI Engineer – Generative AI (SaaS)

Build the Generative AI Future for a Global FinTech/SaaS Leader – Sydney (Hybrid)

Are you an AI pioneer ready to architect the intelligent core of a next-generation financial platform? We are partnering with a global SaaS leader to find a foundational Senior AI Engineer. This is a zero-to-one opportunity to establish and scale their Generative AI ecosystem from the ground up as part of a transformative modernisation programme.

The Mission:
You will be the key technical architect responsible for building the foundational AI capabilities that will define the product's future. Your mission is to design and implement advanced systems, including sophisticated RAG and GraphRAG, to intelligently interpret complex, interconnected financial data. You will ensure these cutting-edge capabilities are not just experimental but are production-ready, secure, and compliant.

The Role:
As the Senior AI Engineer, you will bridge the gap between groundbreaking AI research and robust, scalable engineering. You will own the architecture and implementation of the core GenAI stack, embedding governance and observability from day one to deliver safe, accurate, and differentiating features.

Key Responsibilities:

Architect & Build: Design and build the foundational Generative AI ecosystem, including advanced RAG/GraphRAG systems to query complex structured and unstructured financial data.
Bridge to Production: Create the rigorous framework that transforms AI prototypes into reliable products. This includes designing evaluation methodologies, defining datasets, and implementing automated testing pipelines for safety, accuracy, and regulatory compliance.
Embed Governance: Instil strong MLOps principles, observability, and ethical guardrails from the outset to ensure secure, scalable, and trustworthy AI deployments within a regulated domain.
Collaborate & Lead: Work closely with data scientists, platform engineers, and product teams to integrate AI capabilities that meaningfully enhance this global SaaS platform.
What We're Looking For:

A "been there, done it" expert with deep, hands-on mastery of RAG/LLM architectures and a proven track record of taking AI systems from concept to production.
A strong background in Data Engineering, ML Engineering, or MLOps, with the ability to build robust, scalable infrastructure for AI.
Experience designing rigorous evaluation frameworks, synthetic data generation, and automated testing for AI models.
A strategic thinker who is passionate about both the potential of Generative AI and the engineering discipline required to harness it responsibly.
Proficiency with cloud platforms, ideally AWS (experience with SageMaker, Knowledge Graphs, Databricks, or similar is a strong plus).
Experience in a regulated industry (FinTech, HealthTech, etc.) is a significant advantage.
The Offer:

A pivotal, high-impact role shaping the AI future of a global market leader.
A permanent, full-time position based in Sydney with a balanced hybrid model (3 days in the office, 2 days remote).
The unique opportunity to build a greenfield GenAI ecosystem as part of a major modernisation programme.
Work with a talented team on challenges that blend cutting-edge AI with real-world financial complexity.
Competitive compensation package, including additional days of leave and benefits.

Company Description

About SEEK

SEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities. We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation.

Life at SEEK

SEEK’s purpose is at the centre of everything we do. Our SEEK, which defines the way we work, is all about what makes us unique and a little bit different. Passion, Team, Delivery and Future are our principles that drive innovation and creativity. SEEK strives to support employee wellbeing by providing an amazing experience at work which led us to being named AFR BOSS Top 10 Best Places to Work in Technology (2021-2024). We are proud to work in an environment that's inclusive where everyone's unique ideas, experiences and perspectives are valued.

Our award-winning head office in Cremorne (just a 4 min walk from Richmond station) provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues. The building provides sweeping views of the city, a games area, sit and stand desks at every workstation, modern end-of-trip facilities and Thursday night drinks which gives our people an opportunity to connect in a social setting.

Job Description

The team

At SEEK, our AI Platform Services (AIPS) teams build platforms and solutions that solve complex information problems and enable AI innovation across the SEEK Group. Teams are cross-functional, multi-disciplinary squads that work within an APAC matrix organisational structure. The AI Platform Engineering teams have a specific mission to provide shared infrastructure, governance, and reusable assets that empower AI and product teams to experiment safely, ship faster, and continuously deliver intelligent, differentiated experiences at scale.

You will work with roles across the engineering spectrum from graduate to lead level, including Software Engineers, Engineering Managers, Heads of Engineering, Software Architects, Data Scientists, ML Engineers, Platform Engineers, Product Managers, Business Analysts, and Iteration Managers.

About the role 

A Staff Platform Engineer is a technical lead and senior member within our AI Platform Services (AIPS) Engineering teams. You'll be responsible for the technical strategy and direction of SEEK's GenAI and ML Platforms, ensuring these systems are highly available, resilient, and enable AI innovation at scale. Embedded within a team, you'll lead cross-team technical initiatives that influence AI platform strategy across AIPS and SEEK more broadly. Your primary focus is designing and building AI platform solutions that enable Data Scientists, Engineers, and product teams to deliver AI-powered experiences rapidly and safely. You bring in-depth technical understanding of AI platform infrastructure, multi-cloud architectures (AWS, GCP), and the operational requirements of GenAI and ML systems, while driving alignment of your team's technical roadmap to SEEK's overall AI strategy.
 

Responsibilities 

Design and evolve technical architecture for GenAI and ML platform systems, ensuring they are well-architected, highly available, and aligned with SEEK's development practices and technical metrics
Drive technical strategy that enables SEEK's AI innovation at scale, leading architecture decisions for multi-cloud AI infrastructure (AWS, GCP) and aligning platform capabilities with business objectives
Build and operate highly scalable, performant AI infrastructure using AWS and Python for platform automation, tooling, and integrations while exemplifying clean, well-tested, secure code
Lead cross-team technical initiatives that influence AI platform strategy across AIPS, serving as the key point of contact for technical solutions and system interfaces
Partner with Data Scientists and ML Engineers to enable self-service model development, deployment, and operation while strengthening engineering discipline through understanding of AI/ML operational requirements
Support the Engineering Manager in capacity planning, risk management, and scoping of technical work while building strong relationships with Architecture, Security, and other AI platform teams
Grow team member technical capabilities through coaching on AI/ML platform patterns and practices while fostering a culture of safety, inclusivity, and diversity
Qualifications

Skills and experience 

Proven experience as a Staff Engineer, Principal Engineer, or similar technical leadership role building and operating production platform systems at scale
Strong expertise in cloud infrastructure and platform engineering, with deep hands-on experience in AWS services and multi-cloud architectures
Advanced Python programming skills with demonstrated experience building platform automation, tooling, and integrations for highly scalable systems
Experience with infrastructure-as-code (Terraform), container orchestration (Kubernetes), and observability tools for platform operations
Track record of leading technical roadmaps and driving platform health initiatives aligned with key technical metrics and SRE principles
Experience building platforms that enable self-service capabilities for engineering and data teams, with understanding of developer experience and platform adoption
Hands-on MLOps or ML Engineering experience, GenAI/LLM platform knowledge (model inference, vector databases, RAG patterns), GCP/Vertex AI experience, or ML lifecycle tooling expertise are good to have, but not a must.
Additional Information

Annual Performance Bonus Plan
Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role.
Paid and unpaid leave benefits including Personal Flexi Days and Volunteer Days, as well as the opportunity to purchase additional leave
Support for parents with 14 weeks paid primary carers leave and 2 weeks paid leave for partners
The opportunity to work from anywhere for up to 4 weeks per financial year

About us

Silicon Quantum Computing is pioneering the future of quantum technology. As the world’s first company to manufacture qubits with atomic precision, we’re delivering quantum advantage today, not decades from now.

Founded by Professor Michelle Simmons, one of the world’s leading materials scientists, SQC has achieved major breakthroughs including the first single-atom transistor and the first integrated circuit built with atomic precision. Our Chair, Simon Segars, former CEO of ARM, brings deep global experience as we scale our technology and commercial impact.

Our quantum machine learning chip, Watermelon, is already accelerating AI in ways classical systems can’t match. We’re generating significant revenue and working closely with multinational partners to solve complex problems with quantum solutions.

SQC is a fast-paced, high-accountability environment where people grow quickly and contribute meaningfully. If you’re excited by deep tech, ambitious about your career, and ready to help shape the future of computing, we’d love to hear from you.

About the role

As a Senior Hardware Engineer at SQC, you will play a critical role in the development of quantum computer hardware; working alongside quantum physicists and software engineers in the design, assembly, and testing of our next generation quantum devices. These hardware systems span from room-temperature data acquisition instruments to cryogenic quantum device control and interconnects.

This role will be focused on the design, simulation and integration of low-noise RF electronics and high-speed digital interfaces that make up our advanced measurement systems. This will involve taking responsibility for key technical deliverables, from prototype stage through to system integration and verification. As a senior individual contributor, the position is ideal for someone who thrives on solving complex engineering challenges, takes initiative in technical problem-solving, and is passionate about advancing quantum hardware technology.

Role responsibilities

Design low-noise and RF analog electronic circuits for both room temperature and cryogenic operation.

Develop Printed Circuit Boards (PCBs) using Altium for automating processes in STM device preparation, as well as for custom room temperature measurement instruments and cryogenic cold finger PCBs.

Manage the procurement of components and oversee fabrication processes as required.

Test and verify circuit designs using laboratory equipment such as spectrum analysers, oscilloscopes, function generators, VNAs, and related tools.

Coordinate fabrication (PCB and assembly) for in-house designed test equipment and cryogenic devices/PCBs.

Support the deployment of new in-house developed instrumentation to cryogenic laboratories.

Collaborate with researchers and engineering teams to identify new instrument features and contribute to the development of requirements.

Take ownership of complex hardware projects from concept, through prototyping, to system integration and verification.

Maintain high standards in documentation, design reviews, and project execution to ensure robust and scalable hardware solutions.

Stay abreast of industry trends and relevant emerging technologies.

Mentor and guide others, sharing best practices and standards.

Your experience

Undergraduate degree in Electrical Engineering or a related discipline.

Extensive experience in mixed-signal PCB design and/or RF electronics.

Proven expertise in electronic system design, component selection, PCB layout, circuit population and testing.

Significant experience with using common electronics test equipment (e.g. signal generators, spectrum analysers, network analysers, RF sources, oscilloscopes).

Proficient in commercial simulation software packages (e.g., Altium, LT-Spice, Matlab, ANSYS HFSS, COMSOL).

Excellent organisational skills, attention to detail, and ability to meet deadlines.

Demonstrated ability to work effectively within multidisciplinary teams.

The Carlton Football Club is one of Australia’s oldest and most prominent sport institutions. You will provide systems engineering support focused on verification, validation, and integration activities. Working closely with engineering and project teams, you will help ensure systems meet requirements and are supported by high-quality evidence suitable for formal acceptance.

Support and participate in integration and test activities across complex systems

Perform configuration reviews for hardware and software items

Establish and maintain end-to-end requirements traceability across specifications

Prepare formal test and verification deliverables for review

Minimum 4 years’ experience in Verification & Validation or Systems Engineering roles

Strong hands-on experience decomposing requirements and maintaining traceability from requirement to test, result, and evidence

Experience working with tools such as DOORS, Cameo, Jira, and Confluence

Proven background in integration, verification, and validation of complex software systems and military hardware

Ability to produce clear, concise, and auditable verification evidence for formal acceptance

Desirable

Software development or automated testing experience

Exposure to Defence or safety-critical environments

Security & Location

NV1 security clearance is mandatory

LANMAR supports defence maritime sustainment by delivering and sustaining analytics and decision-support capabilities within the Naval Logistics Information System (NLIS) ecosystem. In this role you will analyse stakeholder needs, design and sustain data models and ETL pipelines, and deliver trusted dashboards and datasets in a controlled Defence environment. Your work must be explainable and auditable – so that metrics and insights are traceable back to source data and changes can be deployed safely through structured governance.  

Key responsibilities: 

Analyse operational and stakeholder needs and translate them into data requirements, KPIs, acceptance criteria and lineage notes.  

Design and maintain SQL Server data models (staging, warehousing/presentation layers) 

Develop and sustain ETL pipelines (e.g., SSIS/TSQL and/or Spark/PySparkSQL), including reconciliation checks, data quality controls, and repeatable run procedures. 

Build and maintain Power BI dashboards and semantic models suitable for enterprise reporting in secure environments. 

Monitor and triage reporting/ETL issues; coordinate investigations and corrective actions with technical teams and stakeholders. 

Produce release artefacts and documentation required for controlled change (impact notes, test evidence, rollback considerations). 

Plan and support functional testing and user acceptance testing (UAT), including test scenario definition and evidence capture. 

Contribute to data governance activities required for future analytics uplift (e.g., documenting data flows, metadata, and candidate datasets for ingestion into enterprise analytics environments when directed). 

 

Skills/Experience 

Strong experience with SQL Server/T-SQL, relational data modelling and basic performance tuning. 

Demonstrated experience delivering Power BI reporting solutions (DAX, Power Query, modelling) 

Experience with ETL tooling such as SSIS (or equivalent) and implementing repeatable, supportable pipelines.  

Experience working in regulated or high-assurance environments (Defence, government, critical infrastructure) with change control and documentation.  

Desirable: SSAS/tabular modelling; asset management/maintenance operations. 

Desirable: Hands-on experience building and supporting Spark/PySpark pipelines (DataFrame/Spark SQL), including joins at scale, partitioning, debugging, and basic performance tuning (shuffles/skew/caching). 

Desirable: Experience working with Iceberg tables (or equivalent lakehouse table formats) including schema/partition evolution, merge/upsert patterns, and designing for governed access (e.g., Ranger-style RBAC/ABAC, audited data lineage). 

 

Security/Clearance  

You must be an Australian citizen and eligible to obtain and maintain an AGSVA security clearance (Baseline or higher). This role operates in secure Defence environments and requires adherence to Defence security policies, controlled change processes and audit-ready documentation.

About Us

With a focus on innovation and delivering better customer outcomes, there has never been a better time to work in the Tasmanian energy sector with Aurora Energy. Be a part of Tasmania’s energy future and make a strong contribution to the ongoing success of our business.
